{{Quote|The bounty hunter is an extremely physically oriented role. One evening I was at a play in Sydney and saw this actress hanging from a bar with one arm while delivering a stunning performance. It was amazing! Leeanna was just who I envisioned for the role. She has this wonderful pixyish, femme fatale look.|Robin Gurland, Episode II Casting Director|<ref name="SWcominterview">{{SWArchive|url=bio/leeannawalsman.html|text=Leeanna Walsman}}</ref>}}
'''Leeanna Walsman''' is an [[Wikipedia:Australians|Australian]] [[Wikipedia:Actress|actress]] who portrayed the [[bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']]. She later reprised her role in the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Bounty Hunter]]'' as well as ''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Skywalker Saga]]''.

Walsman was discovered by [[Robin Gurland]], the casting director for ''Attack of the Clones'', while she was performing with [[Rose Byrne]] ([[Dormé]]) in the play [[Wikipedia:La Dispute|''La Dispute'']] for the [[Wikipedia:Sydney Theatre Company|Sydney Theatre Company]].

Walsman shared screen with ''[[Star Wars]]'' co-star [[Graeme Blundell]] ([[Ruwee Naberrie]]) in the [[2000]] film [[Wikipedia:Looking for Alibrandi (film)|''Looking for Alibrandi'']]. She also worked with [[Joel Edgerton]] ([[Owen Lars]] in Episode II and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]]) and [[Claudia Karvan]] ([[Sola Naberrie]]) in the stop motion film [[Wikipedia:$9.99|''$9.99'']].

